product_review:
Aroma: chocolate, coffee and liqueur in this climate, pleasant unobtrusive alcohol, soy sauce, truffles, some burnt ash;

Appearance: nice but quickly reducing foam, brown clear;

Taste: strong coffee, roastiness, dark chocolate, dry, long pleasant chocolate bitterness, long pleasant aftertastes of dark chocolate;

Palette: medium body, smooth, low carbonation;

Aroma: caramel, raisins, vanilla, noble alcohol, toffee;
Appearance: thick foam quickly reducing, clear, deep copper;
Taste: vanilla, toffee, caramel, raisins, pleasant alcohol, a bit of spice, dry;
Palate: little body, low carbonation, a bit rough;

@Copenhagen Beer Celebration 2016, GREEN

black. Spicy nos.e roasty, bit ashy, spice cabinet, cinnamons, lavender, all sorts. Full bodied. Good bitter cleansing finish. Full flavourful, long linger. Peppercorns.

